<subSubSection id="B6A141D093C39E47848D09F9CB756F7E" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="B296FE09E717D74D2B4C1CEB2C58D124" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B9281DE7424E7AD5DC3B191D3CE4F65B" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
<taxonomicName id="605E6176CB80FEADCE37A67CED4C0B68" authorityName="Mueller" authorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Camponotus tergestinus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tergestinus">
<emphasis id="0CE644C976007BE38D9A437BDB4854FF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Camponotus tergestinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rare arboricolous ant species, nesting in oaks. It has scattered east Mediterranean distribution-from Italy to the Anatolian part of Turkey (
<bibRefCitation id="DBD17076D8EC1E443BD1FABEF876FE9A" author="Marko, B." journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Romanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="29 - 41" refId="B7725925" refString="Marko, B., Ionescu-Hirsch, A., Szasz-Len, A., 2009. Genus Camponotus Mayr, 1861 (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) in Romania: distribution and identification key to the worker caste. Entomologica Romanica 14: 29 - 41" title="Genus Camponotus Mayr, 1861 (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) in Romania: distribution and identification key to the worker caste" volume="14" year="2009">
<normalizedToken id="9ABC62503F8A303192B70CEFA08B99AE" originalValue="Markó">Marko</normalizedToken>
et al. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5E478B9AFE835CD7FD6FECBC5D29F21C" author="Bracko, G." journalOrPublisher="Natura Sloveniae" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="5 - 14" refId="B7725687" refString="Bracko, G., 2017. First discoveries of colonies of the rare ant species Camponotus tergestinus Mueller, 1921 (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) in situ. Natura Sloveniae 19 (2): 5 - 14" title="First discoveries of colonies of the rare ant species Camponotus tergestinus Mueller, 1921 (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) in situ" volume="19" year="2017">
<normalizedToken id="784B702C7A88E26A8AEE6EBA4F1A4F17" originalValue="Bračko">Bracko</normalizedToken>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). In Bulgaria, it was known from only one locality on the southern Black Sea coast (an oak forest near the village of Sinemorets) (
<bibRefCitation id="3FB589050A9F4B9723ABC221F27AD2EF" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="North-Western Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="72 - 84" refId="B7725840" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Kiran, K., 2012. Ant fauna (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) of Strandzha Mountain (Istranca) and adjacent Black Sea coast. North-Western Journal of Zoology 8 (1): 72 - 84" title="Ant fauna (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) of Strandzha Mountain (Istranca) and adjacent Black Sea coast" volume="8" year="2012">Lapeva-Gjonova and Kiran 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
